# .easignore — controls what gets uploaded to the EAS cloud build runner.
# Same syntax as .gitignore. EAS uses .gitignore by default; .easignore
# overrides that when present.
#
# Why this exists: this monorepo has several workspaces (apps/web,
# apps/extension, packages/db) that the mobile app does NOT depend on.
# Uploading them anyway makes the EAS runner run `pnpm install` against
# their dependencies too, including native modules like `sharp` (used by
# the web app for image optimisation). sharp's postinstall fails on the
# EAS Linux runner because no prebuild matches its Node version → the
# whole install fails before iOS native build even starts.
#
# Mobile's actual workspace deps are:
#   - @parking-ticket-pal/constants  (packages/constants)
#   - @parking-ticket-pal/types      (packages/types)
# Everything else can be excluded.

# Other apps — mobile doesn't import any code from these
apps/web/
apps/extension/

# Other packages — mobile doesn't import these either
packages/db/

# Local artifacts and caches that are useless to a clean cloud build
apps/mobile/build-*.ipa
apps/mobile/build-*.apk
apps/mobile/ios/
apps/mobile/android/
apps/mobile/.expo/

# Editor + tooling junk
.vscode/
.claude/
.cursor/
